<br>
That said, I don't mean this as any slight to you, Fuvi, I consider you too a friend.  I just disagree. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
As far as inital AS disbanding and the subsequent formation of SA...<br>
<br>
AS disbanded because the officers, not just Xarpolis, felt that we were putting in too much and getting too little back from the members.  SA was reformed because we realized we were wrong, convinced by the outcry to want to reform guild.  I think maybe 1 or 2 people were uncertain at first about rejoining new guild, and, as far as I know, no one left for another guild.  Overall, it was a big boost of energy for the guild, officers and members alike.  So why the subsequent decay of guild?  One day after SA formation my computer totally died on me, and for the next week I didn't have enough computer access to bother logging on.  Though it sounds immodest, I'm sure my not being around was 99% of the reason for the meltdown.  This is probably because of mistakes I'd made in the past, I had let the guild was too dependent on me, and when I wasn't around, it couldn't function as it usually had, so people were much less motivated to log on and raid and it also limited target selection.  SA, being composed primarily and nearly completely of hardcore raiders, disbanded -- hardcore raiders weren't happy not raiding.<br>
<br>
Anyway, that's just my take.  It really probably was the lvl 40 rangers' beratement that caused our downfall. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>--Lacus<br>Grandmaster<br>
